Package obvious.data

Package obvious.data This package contains the standard interfaces for the Obvious data model.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Data Overarching interface for all classes that contain data.
DataSet Interface DataSet.
Edge Interface Edge.
Forest<V,E> Interface Forest.
Graph<V,E> Graph is a generic Obvious interface containing vertices and edges.
Network Network is a subclass of the generic Graph interface using for nodes and edges classes that derived from Tuple: Node and Edge.
Node This interface subclasses Tuple class.
Schema Schema is an interface describing the columns of a Tuple and by extension of a Table.
Table Table is the basic data structure in Obvious.
Tree<V,E> Tree is a sub-interface of (directed) Graph.
Tuple Tuples are objects representing a row of a data table, providing a simplified interface to table data.
 

Class Summary
DataFactory Abstract Class DataFactory.
 

Enum Summary
Graph.EdgeType Describes two families of graphs.
 

Package obvious.data Description

Package obvious.data

This package contains the standard interfaces for the Obvious data model. It contains the following sub-package : -) obvious.data.event : event package, see corresponding doc -) obvious.data.util : util package, see corresponding doc
